ul.li:
Limit notation indicates that we use a function rule to the left or right of a point
and find the value if that rule were extended continuously to the point of interest.

  \lim_{x \to c^-} f(x) = \text{value from rule on left} 
  \lim_{x \to c^+} f(x) = \text{value from rule on right}

statement.p:
Find the value of a so that
 f(x) = \begin{cases}
  2x+5, & x \le 3, \\
  ax-4, & x \gt 3,
\end{cases}
is continuous at x=3.
